ereotypes and discouraging girls from entering the field. We need to champion narratives that showcase the brilliance and diversity of women in science, highlighting their contributions and achievements. Sharing stories of successful female scientists, celebrating their triumphs, can inspire young girls to dream big and pursue their passions.  This isn't just about numbers; it's about dismantling the illusion that certain fields are inherently " ,
